            <pb id="p02-3" n="3"/>
            <div1 id="BQ-02-1-0002">
                <p>“Blake’s Day” was recently celebrated at the University of Iowa, as reported in an
article by Gail Marshall in <hi rend="u">Middle Earth</hi> (I, 6), an underground newspaper. (Professor Grant
has kindly sent a xerox copy.) The events included readings, “a dance ballet based on <hi rend="u">The Mental
Traveller</hi>” and “a three-piece slide show of Blake’s paintings of saints and serpents flanked by modern
photos of screaming Negroes, machine-gun-shooting Black Berets, and pastoral childhood scenes . . .
accompanied by a tape montage of voices (both adult and child) reading from <hi rend="u">Songs of Innocence
and Experience</hi>, <hi rend="u">Jerusalem</hi>, etc.” Groovy!</p>
            </div1>
        </body>
